# Goldilocks iOS Local Development Environment Configuration
#
# Copy this file to .env. `Scripts/setup.sh` does this for you automatically.
#
# Goldilocks does not use Firebase App Check — the iOS client no longer
# sends an X-Firebase-AppCheck header and the backend wouldn't verify it
# if it did. Build-phase scripts still generate a stable
# `Secrets.FIREBASE_APP_CHECK_DEBUG_TOKEN` constant to keep the generated
# Secrets.swift shape stable for the legacy build configuration; you can
# leave it empty. To re-introduce device attestation, see the security
# plan at docs/plans/2026-05-29-security-hardening.md (item 7).
FIREBASE_APP_CHECK_DEBUG_TOKEN=
